d him; \u201cpackage\u201d means he wasn't the only piece going out, so that return isn't his alone. For the genuinely elite \u2014 who almost never trade, so their only comps are distressed sales \u2014 we show a MODELED estimate of what a player his caliber would command instead."}, "salaryDump": null, "fairContract": {"available": true, "age": 22, "valueWar": 0.33, "rate": 4710846, "terms": [{"years": 2, "endAge": 24, "projectedWar": [0.37, 0.4], "fairAav": 2588676, "totalValue": 5177351}, {"years": 3, "endAge": 25, "projectedWar": [0.37, 0.4, 0.41], "fairAav": 2627933, "totalValue": 7883798}, {"years": 4, "endAge": 26, "projectedWar": [0.37, 0.4, 0.41, 0.4], "fairAav": 2635784, "totalValue": 10543136}, {"years": 5, "endAge": 27, "projectedWar": [0.37, 0.4, 0.41, 0.4, 0.38], "fairAav": 2621651, "totalValue": 13108257}, {"years": 6, "endAge": 28, "projectedWar": [0.37, 0.4, 0.41, 0.4, 0.38, 0.35], "fairAav": 2588676, "totalValue": 15532053}, {"years": 7, "endAge": 29, "projectedWar": [0.37, 0.4, 0.41, 0.4, 0.38, 0.35, 0.32], "fairAav": 2544932, "totalValue": 17814524}, {"years": 8, "endAge": 30, "projectedWar": [0.37, 0.4, 0.41, 0.4, 0.38, 0.35, 0.32, 0.28], "fairAav": 2488570, "totalValue": 19908561}], "note": "Fair AAV = average projected annual market value over the term (aging-curve WAR walk x $4.71M/WAR, each year floored at the league minimum). Longer terms average in decline years, so the fair AAV falls. Real deals carry a term/security premium this does not model -- it is the production-fair anchor, not a prediction of the signing."}, "contractProjection": {"seasonStart": 2027, "status": "RFA", "aavLow": 1046720, "aavMid": 1299856, "aavHigh": 2456714, "capPctMid": 1.1, "term": 1, "comps": [{"name": "Nils Lundkvist", "age": 25, "aav": 1250000, "term": 1, "year": 2025, "status": "RFA"}, {"name": "Adam Wilsby", "age": 25, "aav": 812500, "term": 2, "year": 2025, "status": "RFA"}, {"name": "Victor Mete", "age": 23, "aav": 1200000, "term": 1, "year": 2021, "stat